"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The metric parameter in DBSCAN expects a callable that takes two arrays from X as input and returns a value indicating the distance between them. However, the get_point_distance function is returning a 2D array (the result of euclidean_distances), not a single distance value. This will cause an error when DBSCAN tries to use the metric function.\",\n  \"patch\": \"26c26\\n<    return euclidean_distances([p1.to_list()], [p2.to_list()])\\n---\\n>    return euclidean_distances([p1.to_list()], [p2.to_list()])[0][0]\"\n}"